node.text:
1203 Grove Ter, Dubuque, IA 52001
$799,000, 5 bd, 4 ba, 6,308 sqft

Dubuque's Finest! Grand Victorian "Painted Lady" on bluff with fabulous city and river views. Built by Dubuque's first lumber baron, this home is rich in cherry, walnut, maple & pine woods. Home completely rehabbed in 1992, newer slate roof, copper gutters and fabulous landscaping surround this magnificent home. The beautiful wrap around front porch invites you to watch sunrises, and the city lights in the evening. The current owners have done many quality upgrades and their pride shines thru. Four grand fireplaces, master suite with 17x15 sitting room & 14x10 walk thru closet. Beautiful tiled updated master bath - 18x32 Billiard room can be 5th bedroom.

Listed by:
Deb Hooks
EXIT Realty Dubuque

node.text:
Before and After of the Laurietta House built in 1825 in Mississippi. 
When high school sweethearts Maria Teresa "Tere" and William "Mac" Thomas, married for 39 years, began searching for a getaway near their hometown of New Iberia, Louisiana, Mac, an oil executive, had a hunting camp in mind. After a broker showed him the 680-acre property with rolling, wooded hills and a three-acre lake, he loved everything ... except the broken-down shell of a house that came with the parcel. "It was nothing that a match couldn't cure," jokes Mac. And so began what Tere calls Mac's "gift of love," a three-year gut renovation. Photo by Björn Wallander

node.text: The Hegeler Carus Mansion, located at 1307 Seventh Street in La Salle, Illinois is one of the Midwest's great Second Empire structures. Completed in 1876 for Edward C. Hegeler, a partner in the nearby Matthiessen Hegeler Zinc Company, the mansion was designed in 1874 by noted Chicago architect William W. Boyington. The mansion is now owned and operated by the Hegeler Carus Foundation, and is open to the public. It was designated a National Historic Landmark in 2007. Photo by @stamps.on.my.passport

node.text:
230 Montgomery St, Newburgh, NY 12550
$445,900, 5 bd, 5 ba, 5,472 sqft

Located on Newburgh's East End Historic District, this home offers breathtaking views of the Hudson River and the Newburgh-Beacon Bridge from every floor. Enjoy the magnificent 365 degree views from the light house style office on the top floor. Built in 1900, this brick home boasts 5 bedrooms, 4.5 bathrooms and several fireplaces. Restore this house to the beautiful pre-war charm that it deserves! Close to public transportation, waterfront, restaurants, schools, parks and shops.

Listing by:
Mary Jane Pastor Realty
Dean M Nugent

node.text:
3982 S Lake Park Ave, Chicago, IL 60653
$949,500, 5 bd , 4 ba, 3,300 sqft

Stately greystone on huge 50 x 180 lot! Only 2 owners in 50 years. Currently owned by long time Chicago architect who has loving restored the home maintaining much of it's original virtue. The home features a sprawling open floor plan full of character at every turn. Patterned mahogany wainscoting wrap 3 stunning levels of stairs, intricate ornamental plaster celing inlays, turret rooms, 7 fireplaces, and a turn of the century entry & foyer that will transport you to the golden age of the Chicago greystone. What a beautiful home!  Main level features large updated kitchen adjacent to dining room and just at the rear of the home so perfect for outdoor entertaining. An open parlor connects the dining room to the enormous living room and eventually to the formal entry. The second floor features a large primary suite complete with turret room, enormous walk in closet, and separate water closet/shower & makeup station/sink. Two additional bedrooms with large walk-in closets, a full hall bath, and gracious open space atop the stairs complete the floor. The third floor contains a large open recreation room with lake views! Also additional bedroom and multiple storage/walk-in closets that would make for ideal work from home space. Lower level is partially finished with large open room, kitchenette, potential bedroom, and storage abound. Substantial work has been done to the home over the past 10 years

Listing courtesy of:
Michael Hulett
Jameson Sotheby's Intl Realty

Lauren Bernstein
Jameson Sotheby's Intl Realty
